{{Refimprove|date=March 2007}} [[image:Church in Huambo, Angola.jpg|thumb|250px|Catholic Church in [[Huambo]]]] The '''Catholic Church in Angola''' is part of the worldwide [[Catholic Church]], under the spiritual leadership of the [[Pope]] in [[Rome]]. Approximately 56% (9,486,960)<ref>[[Demography of Angola#Religions]]</ref> of the population profess the Catholic faith, due largely to [[Angola]]'s status as a former [[Portugal|Portuguese]] colony.
There are 19 dioceses, including 5 archdioceses. All the [[bishop]]s are members of the regional [[Episcopal Conference of Angola and São Tomé]].
