'''''Wonderful Ethiopians of the Ancient Cushite Empire''''' is a [[book]] by [[Drusilla Dunjee Houston]] published in 1926.<ref name="Internet Sacred Text Archives">{{cite web |last1=Hare |first1=John Bruno |title=Wonderful Ethiopians of the Ancient Cushite Empire Index |url=http://www.sacred-texts.com/afr/we/index.htm |website=Internet Sacred Text Archives |publisher=Evinity Publishing |accessdate=7 October 2018}}</ref>  The book examines the history of the [[Kingdom of Kush|Cushite]] civilization of [[Africa]].<ref name="suny">{{cite web |title=Wonderful Ethiopians of the Ancient Cushite Empire |url=http://www.sunypress.edu/p-4943-wonderful-ethiopians-of-the-anc.aspx |website=State University of New York Press |accessdate=7 October 2018}}</ref> 

The book is generally considered to have been inspired by [[W. E. B. Du Bois]]'s 1915 book ''[[The Negro]]''.<ref name="Internet Sacred Text Archives"/>

